parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Suspension Failure Causing Bottoming Out and Damage to Undercarriage Components
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the suspension system can cause the vehicle to bottom out, leading to damage to undercarriage components such as water tanks and valves, which can result in costly repairs and potentially leave the vehicle inoperable.
symptoms: The vehicle bottoms out
causing damage to undercarriage components such as water tanks and valves
the springs on the chassis are flattened
the vehicle drifts on the road
the suspension does not absorb shock
and the axle blocks are faulty.
